subtitle: Hello everyone, this is Gene, and welcome back to Astral Doorway, where we explore and seek to
understand all things to do with Astral projection, on this episode i want to talk about one of my
most exhilarating experiences out of the body, it involves me going to one of the deepest
and sinister parts of the lower astral plane that I've ever been to, and i end up meeting humans
who were so unconscious to a point that i didn't even realize was possible
what's more is during this i experienced one of the most dramatic shifts from a lower dimension
to a higher dimension that i've ever had and visited an entirely other planet
inhabited by joyful humanoid-like beings, some of you might be familiar with this experience
already since i've written about it before during the time that it happened but i wanted to
get this on the channel and give my more intimate accounts of this very profound experience which
in some ways i'm still processing due to the shock and sheer significance
of the experience this will probably be one of my longer videos but it's really impossible to
make it short due to the enormity of this astral projection experience otherwise i
just wouldn't be doing it justice, and to the best of my ability
i want you to really feel what i felt during this whole experience
just before i get into that i want to boast about my book and how it's currently number one or quite
high on these new release and bestseller lists on amazon in the categories of out of
body experiences, occult parapsychology, and occult astral projection, if you're interested in the book
check out my recent video on it, maybe it's for you, and maybe it can help you in some way - and
also check out the reviews on amazon people have left some very descriptive and relevant reviews
which i'm grateful for, we're also basically at 1000 subscribers now on this channel so thank you
everyone for subscribing, if you're not subscribed already please do so, episodes are every saturday
so let's get to it this experience started in a vivid but mostly unconscious dream; i was with a
group of friends walking around a city at night we went to a few places, one of them being a jazz bar
in the jazz bar i was talking to people as well as eating some food that i ordered from the bar
now when we decided to leave the jazz bar, my group of friends walked on ahead of me down a road but
because i was so focused on eating my food i lost sight of them, when i realized this i began looking
for them down dark alleys and city streets the roads started to become more creepy with the odd
dark figure here and there and i started to feel a bit of fear in this dream, not the kind of fear
where you know it turns into a nightmare and you start screaming uncontrollably but the opposite
i responded to my fear in a sort of be awake now type of response, right? to be cautious and aware
so this feeling of fear instinctively jolted me into a "hyper security lockdown" mode you could
say, and i jumped into lucidity - the fear was so powerful that upon becoming lucid i immediately
broke the dream to turn it into astral projection, and now usually when i dissolve a dream
and enter the astral plane in that way, i usually enter a pleasant or normal astral dimension but
i guess since this entrance into the astral was mostly based out of fear you could say
i entered into a very desolate and hostile part of the lower astral - if you want to learn how to
break dreams or dissolve them in this way just check out my video on the screen now
which is about how to turn lucid dreams into astral projection, so in the dream i was in a dark
city of mostly black and gray colors, but now i was in a crumbling fiery post-apocalyptic city
of smoky black and red colors - the red and orange hue was mostly from little pockets of fire i saw
here and there in buildings, i did not like where i was especially because i intended to get out of
this type of eerie surroundings right? that was the purpose of getting out of that lucid dream so that
i could get out of those dark alleyways and into a more normal astral plane but the complete opposite
happened and i ended up in the lower astral, but it's funny right? how i was previously already
in a dark city so was my dream an indication that my consciousness was already inadvertently
and unconsciously traveling around in this sort of dimension? but now with the awakening of my
consciousness i saw it in a truer light... who knows, but anyhow this astral dimension i found myself in
i don't know how to describe it there was like a disgusting grunge and insidiousness in the air, it
was horrible i would never want to go there or wish for anyone to go there, everywhere i looked
there was crumbling and damaged cement on the buildings and pavements and the air was
filled with this ominous black smoke which filled the entire sky, it just looked like death
anyway staying in the most zen-like state of mind that i usually do while out of body, which was even
more important to do in this dimension, i continue to walk down more streets just to see what i could
find i passed a lot of abandoned shops and pubs and restaurants all with just this eerie
atmosphere and fire here and there, it looked very english like london in the dark ages, eventually as
i carried on exploring i walked around a corner to a large open courtyard area, and i saw people
walking around in a slow and strange manner, they were all walking individually and aimlessly
like they were drunk, and on closer inspection i was shocked to realize they looked like they were
diseased people who belonged in a hospital or better yet a graveyard, the best way i can
describe them is that they were literally zombies; completely unconscious individuals
with very little sign of intelligence, if at all, any - they literally were "the walking dead" i always
thought typical hollywood movies of zombies were just an over exaggerated reflection of humanity's
lower forms of consciousness but no, here i was watching it in the most direct and real way
this is a sad situation really and reflecting on it now i contemplate the lives of those
individuals but at the time of the experience there i was in the lower astral plane
and my kind of animal instinctive side was on high alert, you know i was only concerned about being
very cautious about how i should proceed next but i wasn't that fearful actually because
of course i was intending not to be fearful but also because if you listen to my previous video
i've met scarier and ill-intended beings before who actually had intention and intelligence but
these zombie-like people looked so feeble that they didn't seem like much of a threat, actually i
considered if i could help these people who i knew, deep down, were really just completely lost souls
as i was looking at this area of mindless zombies walking around, one of them noticed
me he looked at me, and i also took a good look at him, his entire body face arms hands and legs
had rashes scars and blood on them and his skin was overall gray as if he was a lifeless
corpse, his clothes were torn ragged and dirty, i then looked at him as an overall being and
i looked into his eyes to try and catch a glimpse of some form of astral telepathy right? i did
perhaps see some life, some humanness, deep down in his eyes locked away somewhere but it was hard
to connect with him because on the surface was just this strong guarded emotion of malice and
hostility... people have asked me you know since these beings are in a concrete city wearing human
clothes it heavily suggests that they were once normal people so how do you think they got there?
honestly i'm not entirely sure, maybe someone in the comments has a better idea, but like i said i
didn't get a clear reading from them and i didn't have time either as you'll see what happens next
but what i can speculate on is, you know, these are people suffering in the lower astral, not because
they were sent here because of some divine law, but because of personal karma right? personal cause
and effect - they're there not so much because of something they did but as a result of the
way they were or have lived their life for many years i assume, perhaps they lived an extremely
angry or depressed life but what i think is more plausible is that it's something to do with
addiction, more particularly drug abuse or perhaps they were alcoholics but more likely something to
do with being heroin addicts and i've seen these sort of people in the physical too i don't know
where you live but i used to live in the north of the uk in a city where there were a lot of
drug addicts roaming around on the streets, the impressions i got from them are really not
that different from these zombie-like people in the astral if you've ever seen homeless
drug addicts who are on some real bad hard drugs like heroin or spice walking around like zombies
talking garbage harassing people then you'll know what i mean, anyhow getting back to this
particular zombie friend where we were stood looking at each other i considered for a moment if
i could talk to him but he then began to suddenly run at me with this unearthly growl, i didn't run
because i wasn't just going to be chased in the astral right? that would probably end up in all
sorts of mayhem, maybe with a horde following me or something, yeah i just stood there and
as he got within inches of me without thinking i instinctively raised my hand towards him and
i cast a force of light which threw him backwards and into the air and he fell on the ground about
50 feet away from me i knew that once he got up he was probably going to come straight back for me
and others probably would too so i intended to just you know get the hell out of there, i intended
to leave and not run away but in a dimensional shift sense right, and so upon intending to
leave i found myself traveling down under the ground and as i started falling deep underground
i heard this very infernal demonic voice in my ear and i realized i was traveling in
the totally wrong direction now, i'll admit at this point that struck a big chord of fear in me
if i was going even lower in this dimension i didn't even want to think about where i'd
go next, and so with that fear i plucked up all my meditative focus and with pure willpower and
determination i chanted the mantra "OM" and at the same time i forcefully flew upwards as fast and as
powerfully as i could, you know if you're ever trying something in the astral and you ever think
it's not working, whatever it is, and you've tried everything else then just simply use pure
force pure strength and sheer will i guarantee if you have enough fortitude and willpower you
can do almost anything, so with this forced intent i flew back up through the ground and continued
high in the sky and i saw my zombie friend and the crowd of other zombies beneath me and they became
smaller as i flew faster upwards and gaining speed now the fear that i got from that dimension
and the desire to escape it must have become so great and given me such a powerful surge of energy
because the next part blew my mind - as i was flying upwards i was still in that state of mind of
you know get the hell out of there and i was still continuously loudly mantralizing the mantra, "OOMMM"
and as i did i continued to just intend to go faster and faster and as high
as i could now i've done this technique to go to a higher dimension before and usually i'll do it
and arrive at a normal and pleasant dimension of the middle or higher astral in an earth-like
dimension but this time it's like i had this enormous propelling momentum that i couldn't stop
and i didn't want to stop, as i traveled faster and faster i experienced the whole energy of myself
sort of merged into this vibrating celestial consciousness and i actually felt my head or crown
chakra you could say, start to open and expand and this sensation went down through my entire
body i felt this as me penetrating the earth's atmosphere and entering space's cosmic energy
at this point i felt myself without a body and i was just pure vibrating, travelling, awareness
i've never felt a shift or energy like this so consciously and detailed - i was enjoying it i loved
it and i let the whole sensation take over me i became one with it and i clearly intended to go as
far through the stars as i possibly could; i then seemed to go into a hyper-speed type of traveling
and i intensely and vividly experienced my consciousness shift through a sort of interstellar
tunnel and as i traveled through it i saw stars, planets, asteroids, and colorful space clouds go
past me or i was going past them; because what's interesting is that at first it felt as though
i was moving forward at a fast speed right? and i was moving past everything but actually i began
to feel as though instead of me moving forward, matter and objects moved past me instead - it was a
peculiar sensation - this is basically what science would call wormhole - travel wormhole in the sense
that to travel to one place to another space and time bends for you instead of you traveling from
A to B as we usually do in physical life like the diagram on the screen - as this incredible voyage
was happening the sensation of myself began to become more still and i then eventually saw this
neon blue sapphire planet in front of me, i tried to look online for the closest depiction of this
planet that i could find and this was the best one - once i saw this planet, i had a moment of
calm unconsciousness for a moment and then i found myself back in my usual form in a bright
white room in a tall building, it must have been about 40 stories up, the room was immaculate
with all white furniture and i was looking out at this wide floor-length window overlooking the
most beautiful and majestic vastness of crystal clear blue ocean i'd ever seen - i just stood there
taking in this amazing view far in the horizon just above the sea there was this golden light
and as i looked upwards the sky dispersed in color into this golden neon blue gradient
it's really like nothing i've ever seen before, it was inspiring, if i could take a picture
for artists to see i wish i could draw it, yeah i'm getting goosebumps just recalling it now
it was just pure radiance, if anyone ever needs healing i recommend this place
pain just cannot exist in such a place - it just felt like pure life force from this expanse
of nature i guess even a picture wouldn't do it justice because it emanated feelings of joy and
love too, as i looked down more closely towards the building i was in there was this island
in the middle of the ocean with beautiful and colorful tropical-like trees and vegetation that i
didn't recognize but looked very interesting and what i saw next even closer to me
were these huge sea creatures the size of whales swimming in groups, they were stunning
and this species of sea creature looked like a mix of a whale, a koi fish, and a goldfish at the same
time and then i noticed these people or humanoids, for a better word, they were swimming in the ocean
with these giant fish and some of them were even going around in boat-like vehicles and there were
others on platforms floating on the sea and they were diving into the water and they were all just
having all sorts of fun having the absolute time of their lives now i couldn't get a very close
look at them because i was so high up but they seemed to be quite tall, 7 or 8
feet tall and i don't think they had much hair and were clearly very good and flexible swimmers
i would have gone down to see them but i didn't want to intrude, you know, even though these beings
were alien to me i was in fact the one who felt alien and i didn't want to draw any attention
to myself but anyhow i was enjoying myself and i felt pure joy and pure happiness and playfulness
from these beings that i was observing, and what was interesting is i sensed that they had a very
close bond with those giant sea creatures, even though the creatures were big they were gentle
with these humanoid people they would jump in the air over them and i would hear the people
cheering with their arms in the air as the fish went over them, yeah the whole scene was amazing
to see their energy and laughter was uplifting and peaceful, this place was just wonderful and i
found myself just smiling and observing them the positive energy was infectious, any fear that i
had before had long passed, it was such a stark contrast to the previous place i had just been to
in the lower astral, but why did i end up here out of anywhere else in the vastness of space?
actually my interests in astral projection haven't lied much in visiting other planets or aliens
i've never been that interested in humanoid-like species or oceanic planets like this one
so this was all bizarre and new to me, so yeah as i was looking at them i eventually looked around
my room that i was in and i saw a holographic screen on a wall to the left of me which had a
map and a little indicator with some alien text on it that i didn't recognize but i was pretty sure
it was indicating my location, of course i didn't recognize where i was and most of it
was just water, i remember it quite clearly i could probably draw it on a map, but yes the fact
that it was mostly water made me realize this was definitely mostly a water-based planet much
like the many oceanic "exoplanets" that scientists are discovering at the moment now this feeling of
being on another planet became even stronger when i saw their moon in the sky towards the very right
of the window, it was maybe triple the size of our moon and it was bright - but when i say bright
i mean as bright as a star - it was so bright that it had solar flares beaming from its sides
like it was a hot moon, if that is even considered possible amongst modern physics, i was baffled and
was trying to figure out if the sun was behind it or if their sun was close by, but as i stared at it
i began to feel off-balanced and as i did i heard a female voice in the room next to me, she started
telling me about this place but unfortunately i was losing consciousness i could almost make out
her appearance next to me at the other side of the room but i couldn't because i could feel myself
about to either lose the experience or wake up, i just told her that i had to go because i felt
myself losing energy, but even though i couldn't see her i could feel her smiling at me and i felt
feelings of warmth and love from her, and she was the last memory that i had of this place i sort of
just lost the tuning of that frequency, you could say, i didn't struggle for long to try and stay
there i let myself go, i didn't wake up immediately like i do sometimes, there was this peaceful
and slow transition of my awareness coming back to my physical body, perhaps because of how far
away i was from my physical body i don't know, but once i eventually woke up i recalled everything
all the way up to when i was in a dream in the jazz bar and going to see those zombie beings
the fact that i was in a hotel like building with a screen with my location and a huge viewing
window made me feel like this was designed for visitors, perhaps other astral visitors
and this planet felt like happiness and leisure was a usual way of life there, it felt very light
and positive, a lot different from earth basically whilst recalling the experience i
had a sense that i had maybe been to that planet before in some form or another - the woman in the
room with me at the end of the experience felt familiar maybe i had a past life there
or i've unconsciously visited the place before i don't know, maybe that's the reason i went there
out of anywhere else in the galaxy - because by getting a jolt of fear in the lower astral perhaps
a deeper part of me wanted to go to somewhere familiar, somewhere safe, positive and happy
two things come to mind the most out of this experience: one is the peculiarity of the moon
and how it shined like a sun and the other is who were those highly positive humanoid-like
aquatic species? if any of you have insights at all i'm very interested in your comments which i
always read, a few people have said things like it is actually possible for moons to glow like that
i know that i think one of jupiter's moons is a very hot moon with lots of volcanoes on it if
that's correct? and other people have said that the species i saw are related to "mer-people" so like
mermaids and mermen? someone also said that i visited Sirius B, a star system, i think
and that those beings are in a transitional stage between 5th and 6th density, you know
i appreciate absolutely any interpretation so let me know if you have any ideas
so i hope you enjoyed this account of one of my most profound experiences
i really am still processing it in some ways and i hope i can remember to carry the intention to
investigate that planet more in the future, and yes this experience is also just one example of how
we can gain interesting experiences in the lower astral and you know instead of acting out of fear
we can calmly proceed to more profound levels of reality if we act in a calm and deliberate
way so thank you for listening to this longer type of video most of my videos are probably half the
length, if you'd like to support the channel on patreon there's a link in the description below
and if you'd like to have similar experiences like this yourself or you're just learning
how to astral project, i recently made a video on a step-by-step guide on how to astral project maybe
that will help you on your path to these out of body realizations of consciousness, i hope you all
have your own dimensional shifts in consciousness and i will see you on the astral plane
